', \'with\', \'the\', \'reasons\', \'that\', \'have\', \'induced\', \'him\', \'to\', \'write\']',4),(65,'나는 내 마음이 일반인들보다 어떤 면에서 더 완벽하다고 생각한 적이 없으며, 오히려 생각의 신속성이나 상상력의 명료함과 뚜렷함, 기억의 충만함과 준비성에서 다른 사람들과 동등하기를 종종 바랐던 적이 있습니다.','for myself, i have never fancied my mind to be in any respect more perfect than those of the generality; on the contrary, i have often wished that i were equal to some others in promptitude of thought, or in clearness and distinctness of imagination, or in fullness and readiness of memory.',1637,2008,'290','[\'for\', \'myself\', \'have\', \'never\', \'fancied\', \'my\', \'mind\', \'to\', \'be\', \'in\', \'any\', \'respect\', \'more\', \'perfect\', \'than\', \'those\', \'of\', \'the\', \'generality\', \'on\', \'the\', \'contrary\', \'have\', \'often\', \'wished\', \'that\', \'were\', \'equal\', \'to\', \'some\', \'others\', \'in\', \'promptitude\', \'of\', \'thought\', \'or\', \'in\', \'clearness\', \'and\', \'distinctness\', \'of\', \'imagination\', \'or\', \'in\', \'fullness\', \'and\', \'readiness\', \'of\', \'memory\']',4),(66,'선한 감각은 인간에게 있는 모든 것 중에서 가장 균등하게 분배되어 있는데, 모든 사람은 자신이 그것을 너무 풍부하게 공급받았다고 생각하기 때문에 다른 모든 면에서 가장 만족하기 어려운 사람들도 일반적으로 이미 가지고 있는 것보다 더 많은 양을 원하지 않습니다.','good sense is, of all things among men, the most equally distributed; for every one thinks himself so abundantly provided with it, that those even who are the most difficult to satisfy in everything else, do not usually desire a larger measure of this quality than they already possess.',1637,2008,'286','[\'good\', \'sense\', \'is\', \'of\', \'all\', \'things\', \'among\', \'men\', \'the\', \'most\', \'equally\', \'distributed\', \'for\', \'every\', \'one\', \'thinks\', \'himself\', \'so\', \'abundantly\', \'provided\', \'with\', \'it\', \'that\', \'those\', \'even\', \'who\', \'are\', \'the\', \'most\', \'difficult\', \'to\', \'satisfy\', \'in\', \'everything\', \'else\', \'do\', \'not\', \'usually\', \'desire\', \'larger\', \'measure\', \'of\', \'this\', \'quality\', \'than