e slightest particular, they subject themselves to censure.',1637,2008,'219','[\'they\', \'who\', \'set\', \'themselves\', \'to\', \'give\', \'precepts\', \'must\', \'of\', \'course\', \'regard\', \'themselves\', \'as\', \'possessed\', \'of\', \'greater\', \'skill\', \'than\', \'those\', \'to\', \'whom\', \'they\', \'prescribe\', \'and\', \'if\', \'they\', \'err\', \'in\', \'the\', \'slightest\', \'particular\', \'they\', \'subject\', \'themselves\', \'to\', \'censure\']',4),(75,'나는 우리가 자신과 관련된 것에 대해 얼마나 망상에 빠지기 쉬운지, 또한 우리에게 유리하게 주어질 때 친구들의 판단을 얼마나 의심해야 하는지 잘 알고 있습니다.','i know how very liable we are to delusion in what relates to ourselves, and also how much the judgments of our friends are to be suspected when given in our favor.',1637,2008,'163','[\'know\', \'how\', \'very\', \'liable\', \'we\', \'are\', \'to\', \'delusion\', \'in\', \'what\', \'relates\', \'to\', \'ourselves\', \'and\', \'also\', \'how\', \'much\', \'the\', \'judgments\', \'of\', \'our\', \'friends\', \'are\', \'to\', \'be\', \'suspected\', \'when\', \'given\', \'in\', \'our\', \'favor\']',4),(76,'그러나 이 글은 단지 역사로서, 또는 원한다면 이야기로서, 본받을 만한 가치가 있는 몇 가지 사례들 가운데 아마도 따르지 않는 것이 더 많은 사례들이 발견될 것이므로, 나는 그것이 누구에게도 해가 되지 않고 어떤 사람들에게는 유용할 것이며, 나의 개방성이 모든 사람들에게 호의를 얻을 수 있기를 바랍니다.','but as this tract is put forth merely as a history, or, if you will, as a tale, in which, amid some examples worthy of imitation, there will be found, perhaps, as many more which it were advisable not to follow, i hope it will prove useful to some without being hurtful to any, and that my openness will find some favor with all.',1637,2008,'329','[\'but\', \'as\', \'this\', \'tract\', \'is\', \'put\', \'forth\', \'merely\', \'as\', \'history\', \'or\', \'if\', \'you\', \'will\', \'as\', \'tale\', \'in\', \'which\', \'amid\', \'some\', \'examples\', \'worthy\', \'of\', \'imitation\', \'there\', \'will\', \'be\', \'found\', \'perhaps\', \'as\', \'many\', \'more\', \'which\', \'it\', \'were\', \'advisable\', \'not\', \'to\', \'follow\', 