stand\', \'the\', \'expression\', \'being\']',11),(361,'\'순수 이성\'은 첫 번째 작업에서 동일한 용어를 사용한 경우와 마찬가지로 이론적 사용에서의 이성을 나타내기 위한 것일 뿐이며, 실제 이성으로서의 기능과 그 특수 원칙을 검토하려는 의도는 없지만 허용될 수 있습니다.','this is permissible although \'pure reason\', as was the case with the same use of terms in our first work, is only intended to denote reason in its theoretical employment, and although there is no desire to bring under review its faculty as practical reason and its special principles as such.',1790,2007,'292','[\'this\', \'is\', \'permissible\', \'although\', \'pure\', \'reason\', \'as\', \'was\', \'the\', \'case\', \'with\', \'the\', \'same\', \'use\', \'of\', \'terms\', \'in\', \'our\', \'first\', \'work\', \'is\', \'only\', \'intended\', \'to\', \'denote\', \'reason\', \'in\', \'its\', \'theoretical\', \'employment\', \'and\', \'although\', \'there\', \'is\', \'no\', \'desire\', \'to\', \'bring\', \'under\', \'review\', \'its\', \'faculty\', \'as\', \'practical\', \'reason\', \'and\', \'its\', \'special\', \'principles\', \'as\', \'such\']',12),(362,'따라서 우선 이 질문의 의미에 대한 이해를 다시 한 번 되새겨야 합니다.','so first of all we must reawaken an understanding for the meaning of this question.',1927,1996,'83','[\'so\', \'first\', \'of\', \'all\', \'we\', \'must\', \'reawaken\', \'an\', \'understanding\', \'for\', \'the\', \'meaning\', \'of\', \'this\', \'question\']',11),(363,'다음 글에서 우리의 목표는 존재의 의미에 대한 질문을 구체적으로 풀어내는 것입니다.','our aim in the following treatise is to work out the question of the meaning of being and to do so concretely.',1927,1996,'110','[\'our\', \'aim\', \'in\', \'the\', \'following\', \'treatise\', \'is\', \'to\', \'work\', \'out\', \'the\', \'question\', \'of\', \'the\', \'meaning\', \'of\', \'being\', \'and\', \'to\', \'do\', \'so\', \'concretely\']',11),(364,'그렇다면 이러한 비판은 단순히 선험적으로 사물을 알고 있는 우리의 교수진에 대한 조사입니다.','that critique is, then, an investigation addressed simply to our faculty of knowing things a priori.',1790,2007,'100','[\'that\', \'critique\', \'is\', \'then\', \'an\', \'inv