 지키겠다\'고 스스로에게 말한다면 더 안전하게 이 행동을 할 수 있습니다.','and thus you will more safely go about this action if you say to yourself, \'i will now go to bathe and keep my own will in harmony with nature.\'',125,2014,'144','[\'and\', \'thus\', \'you\', \'will\', \'more\', \'safely\', \'go\', \'about\', \'this\', \'action\', \'if\', \'you\', \'say\', \'to\', \'yourself\', \'will\', \'now\', \'go\', \'to\', \'bathe\', \'and\', \'keep\', \'my\', \'own\', \'will\', \'in\', \'harmony\', \'with\', \'nature\']',19),(600,'다른 모든 행동도 마찬가지입니다.','and so with regard to every other action.',125,2014,'41','[\'and\', \'so\', \'with\', \'regard\', \'to\', \'every\', \'other\', \'action\']',19),(601,'그러므로 목욕하는 데 장애가 생기면 \'내가 원한 것은 목욕하는 것만이 아니라 내 뜻을 자연과 조화롭게 지키기 위함이었으며, 만약 내가 사물에 유머를 잃으면 이렇게 지키지 않으리라\'고 말할 수 있을 것이다.','for thus, if any impediment arises in bathing, you will be able to say, \'it was not only to bathe that i desired, but to keep my will in harmony with nature; and i shall not keep it thus if i am out of humor at things that happen.\'',125,2014,'231','[\'for\', \'thus\', \'if\', \'any\', \'impediment\', \'arises\', \'in\', \'bathing\', \'you\', \'will\', \'be\', \'able\', \'to\', \'say\', \'it\', \'was\', \'not\', \'only\', \'to\', \'bathe\', \'that\', \'desired\', \'but\', \'to\', \'keep\', \'my\', \'will\', \'in\', \'harmony\', \'with\', \'nature\', \'and\', \'shall\', \'not\', \'keep\', \'it\', \'thus\', \'if\', \'am\', \'out\', \'of\', \'humor\', \'at\', \'things\', \'that\', \'happen\']',19),(602,'인간은 사물이 아니라 사물을 바라보는 관점에 의해 방해를 받습니다.','men are disturbed not by things, but by the views which they take of things.',125,2014,'76','[\'men\', \'are\', \'disturbed\', \'not\', \'by\', \'things\', \'but\', \'by\', \'the\', \'views\', \'which\', \'they\', \'take\', \'of\', \'things\']',19),(603,'따라서 죽음은 소크라테스에게 끔찍한 것이 아니며, 그렇지 않았다면 그렇게 보였을 것입니다.','thus death is nothing terrible, else it would have appeared so to socrates.',125,2014,'75','[\'thus\', \'death\', \'is\', \'nothing\', \'terrible\', \'else\', \'it\', \'would\', \'have\', \'appeared\', \'so\', \'to\', \'socrates\']',19),(604,'하지만 공포는 죽음에 대한 우리의 관념, 즉 끔찍하다는 생각에서 비롯됩니다.','but the terror consists in our notion of death, that it is terrible.',125,2014,'68','[\'but\', \'the\', \'terror\', \'consists\', \'in\', \'our\', \'notion\', \'of\', \'death\', \'that\', \'it\', \'is\', \'terrible\']',19),(605,' 네가 스스로 즐거워할 때마다 너와 함께 사는 자들 가운데서 네가 본 좋은 부분과 특별한 은사를 생각하고 묵상하라, 곧 하나는 산업, 다른 하나는 겸손, 다른 하나는 풍성함, 다른 하나는 다른 어떤 것에서 보았느니라.',' whensoever thou wilt rejoice thyself, think and meditate upon those good parts and especial gifts, which thou hast observed in any of them that live with thee: as industry in one, in another modesty, in another bountifulness, in another some other thing.',170,2008,'255','[\'whensoever\', \'thou\', \'wilt\', \'rejoice\', \'thyself\', \'think\', \'and\', \'meditate\', \'upon\', \'those\', \'good\', \'parts\', \'and\', \'especial\', \'gifts\', \'which\', \'thou\', \'hast\', \'observed\', \'in\', \'any\', \'of\', \'them\', \'that\', \'live\', \'with\', \'thee\', \'as\', \'industry\', \'in\', \'one\', \'in\', \'another\', \'modesty\', \'in\', \'another\', \'bountifulness\', \'in\', \'another\', \'some\', \'other\', \'thing\']',20),(606,'너와 함께 사는 여러 미덕의 닮은 점과 비슷한 점, 특히 그들이 한꺼번에 너에게 자신을 나타내는 것만큼 너를 기쁘게 할 수 있는 것은 아무것도 없기 때문이다.','for nothing can so much rejoice thee, as the resemblances and parallels of several virtues, eminent in the dispositions of them that live with thee, especially when all at once, as it were, they represent themselves unto thee.',170,2008,'226','[\'for\', \'nothing\', \'can\', \'so\', \'much\', \'rejoice\', \'thee\', \'as\', \'the\', \'resemblances\', \'and\', \'parallels\', \'of\', \'several\', \'virtues\', \'eminent\', \'in\', \'the\', \'dispositions\', \'of\', \'them\', \'that\', \'live\', \'with\', \'thee\', \'especially\', \'when\', \'all\', \'at\', \'once\', \'as\', \'it\', \'were\', \'they\', \'represent\', \'themselves\', \'unto\', \'thee\']',20),(607,'그러므로 항상 준비 태세를 갖추도록 하십시오.','see therefore, that thou have them always in a readiness.',170,2008,'57','[\'see\', \'therefore\', \'that\', \'thou\', \'have\', \'them\', \'always\', \'in\', \'readiness\']',20),(608,'할아버지 베루스에게서 온화하고 온유하며 모든 분노와 정열을 자제하는 법을 배웠습니다.','of my grandfather verus i have learned to be gentle and meek, and to refrain from all anger and passion.',170,2008,'104','[\'of\', \'my\', \'grandfather\', \'verus\', \'have\', \'learned\', \'to\', \'be\', \'gentle\', \'and\', \'meek\', \'and\', \'to\', \'refrain\', \'from\', \'all\', \'anger\', \'and\', \'passion\']',20),(609,'나를 낳은 그분의 명성과 기억으로부터','from the fame and memory of him that begot me',170,2008,'45','[\'from\', \'the\', \'fame\', \'and\', \'memory\', \'of\', \'him\', \'that\', \'begot\', \'me\']',20),(610,'저는 부끄러움과 남자다운 행동을 모두 배웠습니다.','i have learned both shamefastness and manlike behaviour.',170,2008,'56','[\'have\', \'learned\', \'both\', \'shamefastness\', \'and\', \'manlike\', \'behaviour\']',20),(611,'어머니에게서 나는 종교적이고 풍요로운 것을 배웠으며, 악을 행할 뿐만 아니라 악을 도모하는 것을 참으며, 여분의 음식으로 만족하고, 큰 부에 부수되는 모든 과잉을 날려 버리는 것을 배웠습니다.','of my mother i have learned to be religious, and bountiful; and to forbear, not only to do, but to intend any evil; to content myself with a spare diet, and to fly all such excess as is incidental to great wealth.',170,2008,'213','[\'of\', \'my\', \'mother\', \'have\', \'learned\', \'to\', \'be\', \'religious\', \'and\', \'bountiful\', \'and\', \'to\', \'forbear\', \'not\', \'only\', \'to\', \'do\', \'but\', \'to\', \'intend\', \'any\', \'evil\', \'to\', \'content\', \'myself\', \'with\', \'spare\', \'diet\', \'and\', \'to\', \'fly\', \'all\', \'such\', \'excess\', \'as\', \'is\', \'incidental\', \'to\', \'great\', \'wealth\']',20),(612,'증조부께서 공립학교와 청각을 자주 다니게 하시고, 집에서 훌륭하고 유능한 선생님을 모시게 하셨으며, 그런 일이 있을 때 내가 과중한 책임을 지더라도 크게 생각하지 말라고 하셨습니다.','of my great grandfather, both to frequent public schools and auditories, and to get me good and able teachers at home; and that i ought not to think much