nt of the others; but that you must entirely quit some of them, and for the present postpone the rest.',125,2014,'237','[\'aiming\', \'therefore\', \'at\', \'such\', \'great\', \'things\', \'remember\', \'that\', \'you\', \'must\', \'not\', \'allow\', \'yourself\', \'any\', \'inclination\', \'however\', \'slight\', \'toward\', \'the\', \'attainment\', \'of\', \'the\', \'others\', \'but\', \'that\', \'you\', \'must\', \'entirely\', \'quit\', \'some\', \'of\', \'them\', \'and\', \'for\', \'the\', \'present\', \'postpone\', \'the\', \'rest\']',19),(817,'그러나 이것들을 가지고 권력과 부도 함께 소유한다면, 전자를 추구하다가 후자를 놓칠 수 있으며, 그것만으로 행복과 자유를 얻는 데 실패할 것이 분명합니다.','but if you would have these, and possess power and wealth likewise, you may miss the latter in seeking the former; and you will certainly fail of that by which alone happiness and freedom are procured.',125,2014,'201','[\'but\', \'if\', \'you\', \'would\', \'have\', \'these\', \'and\', \'possess\', \'power\', \'and\', \'wealth\', \'likewise\', \'you\', \'may\', \'miss\', \'the\', \'latter\', \'in\', \'seeking\', \'the\', \'former\', \'and\', \'you\', \'will\', \'certainly\', \'fail\', \'of\', \'that\', \'by\', \'which\', \'alone\', \'happiness\', \'and\', \'freedom\', \'are\', \'procured\']',19),(818,'그러므로 모든 불쾌한 모습에 대해 \'당신은 겉모습일 뿐 결코 진짜가 아닙니다\'라고 말할 수 있도록 즉시 구하십시오.','seek at once, therefore, to be able to say to every unpleasing semblance, \'you are but a semblance and by no means the real thing.\'',125,2014,'131','[\'seek\', \'at\', \'once\', \'therefore\', \'to\', \'be\', \'able\', \'to\', \'say\', \'to\', \'every\', \'unpleasing\', \'semblance\', \'you\', \'are\', \'but\', \'semblance\', \'and\', \'by\', \'no\', \'means\', \'the\', \'real\', \'thing\']',19),(819,'그리고 너희가 가지고 있는 규칙에 따라, 그리고 무엇보다도 이것, 즉 그것이 우리의 힘 안에 있는 것들에 관한 것이든 그렇지 않은 것들에 관한 것이든 살펴보고, 만약 그것이 우리의 힘 밖의 것에 관한 것이라면, 너희에게는 아무것도 아니라고 말할 준비를 하라.','and then examine it by those rules which you have; and first and chiefly by this: whether it concerns the things which are within our own power or those which are not; and if it concerns anything beyond our power, be prepared to say that it is nothing to you.',125,2014,'259','[\'and\', \'then\', \'examine\', \'it\', \'by\', \'those\', \'rules\', \'which\', \'you\', \'have\', \'and\', \'first\', \'and\', \'chiefly\', \'by\', \'this\', \'whether\', \'it\', \'concerns\', \'the\', \'things\', \'which\', \'are\', \'within\', \'our\', \'own\', \'power\', \'or\', \'those\', \'which\', \'are\', \'not\', \'and\', \'if\', \'it\', \'concerns\', \'anything\', \'beyond\', \'our\', \'power\', \'be\', \'prepared\', \'to\', \'say\', \'that\', \'it\', \'is\', \'nothing\', \'to\', \'you\']',19),(820,'욕망은 욕망하는 것을 성취할 것을 요구하고, 혐오는 혐오하는 것을 피할 것을 요구하며, 욕망의 대상에서 실패하는 자는 실망하고, 혐오의 대상을 초래하는 자는 비참하다는 것을 기억하십시오.','remember that desire demands the attainment of that of which you are desirous; and aversion demands the avoidance of that to which you are averse; that he who fails of the object of his desires is disappointed; and he who incurs the object of his aversion is wretched.',125,2014,'268','[\'remember\', \'that\', \'desire\', \'demands\', \'the\', \'attainment\', \'of\', \'that\', \'of\', \'which\', \'you\', \'are\', \'desirous\', \'and\', \'aversion\', \'demands\', \'the\', \'avoidance\', \'of\', \'that\', \'to\', \'which\', \'you\', \'are\', \'averse\', \'that\', \'he\', \'who\', \'fails\', \'of\', \'the\', \'object\', \'of\', \'his\', \'desires\', \'is\', \'disappointed\', \'and\', \'he\', \'who\', \'incurs\', \'the\', \'object\', \'of\', \'his\', \'aversion\', \'is\', \'wretched\']',19),(821,'그러므로 당신이 통제할 수 있는 바람직하지 않은 것들만 피한다면, 당신이 피하는 것은 결코 발생하지 않을 것이지만, 질병이나 죽음이나 가난을 피한다면, 비참한 위험을 초래할 것입니다.','if, then, you shun only those undesirable things which you can control, you will never incur anything which you shun; but if you shun sickness, or death, or poverty, you will run the risk of wretchedness.',125,2014,'204','[\'if\', \'then\', \'you\', \'shun\', \'only\', \'those\', \'undesirable\', \'things\', \'which\', \'you\', \'can\', \'control\', \'you\', \'will\', \'never\', \'incur\', \'anything\', \'which\', \'you\', \'shun\', \'but\', \'if\', \'you\', \'shun\', \'sickness\', \'or\', \'death\', \'or\', \'poverty\', \'you\', \'will\', \'run\', \'the\', \'risk\', \'of\', \'wretchedness\']',19),(822,'그러므로 혐오의 습관을 우리의 힘에 속하지 않는 모든 것에서 제거하고, 우리의 힘에 속하는 바람직하지 않은 것들에 적용하세요.','remove the habit of aversion, then, from all things that are not within our power, and apply it to things undesirable which are within our power.',125,2014,'145','[\'remove\', \'the\', \'habit\', \'of\', \'aversion\', \'then\', \'from\', \'all\', \'things\', \'that\', \'are\', \'not\', \'within\', \'our\', \'power\', \'and\', \'apply\', \'it\', \'to\', \'things\', \'undesirable\', \'which\', \'are\', \'within\', \'our\', \'power\']',19),(823,'그러나 현재로서는 욕망을 모두 자제하라, 우리 힘에 속하지 않는 것을 욕망하면 반드시 실망할 것이요, 우리 힘에 속하는 것을 아직 확보하지 못했기 때문에 정당한 욕망의 대상이다.','but for the present, altogether restrain desire; for if you desire any of the things not within our own power, you must necessarily be disappointed; and you are not yet secure of those which are within our power, and so are legitimate objects of desire.',125,2014,'253','[\'but\', \'for\', \'the\', \'present\', \'altogether\', \'restrain\', \'desire\', \'for\', \'if\', \'you\', \'desire\', \'any\', \'of\', \'the\', \'things\', \'not\', \'within\', \'our\', \'own\', \'power\', \'you\', \'must\', \'necessarily\', \'be\', \'disappointed\', \'and\', \'you\', \'are\', \'not\', \'yet\', \'secure\', \'of\', \'those\', \'which\', \'are\', \'within\', \'our\', \'power\', \'and\', \'so\', \'are\', \'legitimate\', \'objects\', \'of\', \'desire\']',19),(824,'실제로 무언가를 추구하거나 피해야 할 필요가 있는 경우, 이 경우에도 신중하고 온화하고 절제된 태도로 행동하세요.','where it is practically necessary for you to pursue or avoid anything, do even this with discretion and gentleness and moderation.',125,2014,'130','[\'where\', \'it\', \'is\', \'practically\', \'necessary\', \'for\', \'you\', \'to\', \'pursue\', \'or\', \'avoid\', \'anything\', \'do\', \'even\', \'this\', \'with\', \'discretion\', \'and\', \'gentleness\', \'and\', \'moderation\']',19),(825,'마음을 기쁘게 하거나 쓰임에 기여하거나 부드럽게 사랑받는 모든 물건에 대해, 아주 사소한 것부터 시작하여 그것이 어떤 성질을 지니고 있는지를 상기하십시오: 좋아하는 컵이 있다면, 그것은 당신이 좋아하는 컵일 뿐이므로 깨져도 견딜 수 있고, 자녀나 아내를 안고 있다면, 당신은 필멸자를 안고 있는 것이므로 둘 중 하나가 죽어도 견딜 수 있습니다.','with regard to whatever objects either delight the mind or contribute to use or are tenderly beloved, remind yourself of what nature they are, beginning with the merest trifles: if you have a favorite cup, that it is but a cup of which you are fond of for thus, if it is broken, you can bear it; if you embrace your child or your wife, that you embrace a mortal and thus, if either of them dies, you can bear it.',125,2014,'412','[\'with\', \'regard\', \'to\', \'whatever\', \'objects\', \'either\', \'delight\', \'the\', \'mind\', \'or\', \'contribute\', \'to\', \'use\', \'or\', \'are\', \'tenderly\', \'beloved\', \'remind\', \'yourself\', \'of\', \'what\', \'nature\', \'they\', \'are\', \'beginning\', \'with\', \'the\', \'merest\', \'trifles\', \'if\', \'you\', \'have\', \'favorite\', \'cup\', \'that\', \'it\', \'is\', \'but\', \'cup\', \'of\', \'which\', \'you\', \'are\', \'fond\', \'of\', \'for\', \'thus\', \'if\', \'it\', \'is\', \'broken\', \'you\', \'can\', \'bear\', \'it\', \'if\', \'you\', \'embrace\', \'your\', \'child\', \'or\', \'your\', \'wife\', \'that\', \'you\', \'embrace\', \'mortal\', \'and\', \'thus\', \'if\', \'either\', \'of\', \'them\', \'dies\', \'you\', \'can\', \'bear\', \'it\']',19);
